JOHANNESBURG - The consumer price inflation increased to an annual 3.2% in March this year. This signaled a 0.7% month-on-month increase. Economists projected that the rate would increase above 3% following increases in fuel prices in March. The February CPI was 2.9%. CPI #inflation was 3,2% in March 2021, up from 2,9% in February 2021. The #CPI increased by 0,7% m/m in March 2021.Listen here for more: https://t.co/SDz18FyA2j#StatsSA pic.twitter.com/Mw34cJVWYX  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.